Vice President Kamala Harris spoke with Ajay Banga, Executive Chairman of Mastercard, and Jonathan Fantini Porter, Executive Director of the Partnership for Central America (PCA), about their work in El Salvador, Guatemala, and Honduras. They discussed efforts to increase private sector investment and improve livelihoods in the region, in collaboration with the Department of State, USAID, and other agencies. The Vice President also shared her vision for the Root Causes Strategy and the Call to Action she announced in May. She provided updates from her trip to Guatemala and Mexico in June and explored ways to continue working together. Additionally, they discussed her upcoming trip to Singapore and Vietnam.